# Analysis of the Main Target Image

The main target image shows two separate structures placed on a dark checkered floor:

## Structure 1 (Left side):
This is a small house-like structure consisting of:
- A red arch-shaped block at the bottom
- A blue cube block in the middle
- A yellow half-cylinder/tunnel on top of the red block
- An orange triangular roof on top of the blue cube

## Structure 2 (Right side):
This is a more complex arrangement consisting of:
- Two vertical green rectangular blocks (one on each side)
- Two orange cylindrical blocks in the center
- An orange triangular block at the front
- An orange structure with a triangular roof in the middle
- An orange triangular/wedge block at the back

# Block Selection from Dictionary

Based on the Block Dictionary image, I can identify the following blocks needed:

For Structure 1:
- Block #1: Red arch block
- Block #3: Blue cube
- Block #9: Yellow half-cylinder/tunnel
- Block #12: Orange triangular roof piece

For Structure 2:
- Block #4: Green cube (used twice)
- Block #7: Orange vertical cylinder (used twice)
- Block #13: Orange triangular wedge (front)
- Block #12: Orange triangular roof piece (middle)
- Block #15: Orange triangular wedge (back)

# Assembly Order

```
{
    Step1: Move block with index 1
    Step2: Move block with index 3
    Step3: Move block with index 9
    Step4: Move block with index 12
    Step5: Move block with index 4
    Step6: Move block with index 7
    Step7: Move block with index 7
    Step8: Move block with index 12
    Step9: Move block with index 4
    Step10: Move block with index 13
    Step11: Move block with index 15
}
```

This assembly order starts with building the left structure (steps 1-4) and then proceeds to build the right structure (steps 5-11), working from the bottom up and from left to right for each structure.
